%N A395730 Decimal expansion of the maximum area of cross-section of a regular dodecahedron of unit edge length.
%C A395730 The corresponding values for the other Platonic solids with unit-length edges are:
%C A395730   Regular tetrahedron: sqrt(3)/4 (A120011).
%C A395730   Cube: sqrt(2) (A002193).
%C A395730   Regular octahedron: 1.
%C A395730   Regular icosahedron: (2+sqrt(5))/2 (A176055).
%C A395730 The value given by Brandenburg et al. (2025) is for a regular dodecahedron with edge length of 4*(sqrt(5)-2).
%H A395730 Marie-Charlotte Brandenburg, Jesús A. De Loera, and Chiara Meroni, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1090/mcom/4006">The Best Ways to Slice a Polytope</a>, Math. Comp., Vol. 94 (2025), pp. 1003-1042; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2304.14239">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:2304.14239 [math.CO], 2023.
%H A395730 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 04</a>.
%H A395730 <a href="/index/Do#dodecahedron">Index entries for sequences related to dodecahedron</a>.
%F A395730 Equals 5*sqrt((65 + 29*sqrt(5))/2)/8.
%F A395730 Minimal polynomial: 4096*x^4 - 104000*x^2 + 3125.
%e A395730 5.035925066838008718358412386770364959265500972079428...
%t A395730 RealDigits[5*Sqrt[(65 + 29*Sqrt[5])/2]/8, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395730 (PARI) 5*sqrt((65 + 29*sqrt(5))/2)/8
%Y A395730 Cf. A002193, A120011, A176055, A395727, A395728.
